EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

Accidental Release Prevention and Emergency Response Policies:
The Aurorium Zeeland Facility's Prevention Program is composed of the following elements, which are all part of the Process Safety Management (PSM) program. This program follows the requirements set forth in 29 CFR 1910.119:
1) Employees participate in the elements of this safety and release prevention program wherever possible;
2) Adequate training is provided for operators and maintenance personnel;
3) Process Safety Information (PSI) including P&IDs, operating procedures, safe operating limits are maintained on the ethylene system and associated hazards;
4) A Process Hazard Analysis (PHA) of the ethylene system was conducted using HAZOP/What-if methodology and are periodically reviewed to ensure adequacy of controls; 
5) The Mechanical Integrity program ensures the system continues to operate as designed;
6) Operating and Maintenance procedures provide operators and maintenance staff the information necessary to safely operate and maintain the system;
7) Contractors working on or near the ethylene system are selected for safety performance, and are briefed on the hazards and safety requirements of the job;
8) Hot Work Permits are required whenever welding, cutting, grinding or other activities are conducted that could generate sparks and start a fire;
9) The Management of Change (MOC) program is implemented to manage and document changes to the ethylene system and approved prior to the work being conducted;
10) Pre-Startup Safety Reviews (PSSR) are conducted prior to restart of the system after modifications to ensure that impacts of the change are addressed;
11) Incident investigations are conducted for incidents involving ethylene releases and near misses that endanger employees or the public, if such an incident were to occur;
12) Compliance Audits will be conducted every three years to ensure that the prevention program is meeting its objectives;
